      "content": "\"Not being\" doesn't mean disappearing; it means ceasing the fight against the current. It's about accepting that the struggle itself is the exhaustion you feel, and that's okay. If life is this much, then the release comes from stopping the resistance—from letting the heavy weight just settle, instead of constantly trying to push it away. It's a quiet surrender to the fact that you don't have to be perfect or normal to exist.",
